main event: An unidentified object was observed in Watertown, South Dakota on March 30, 1965, for a duration of 3 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as elongated and glowing., The observer reported that it moved rapidly and disappeared., No physical evidence was found to support the sighting., The observer could not provide further details about the object's appearance or behavior., The conclusion from the report classified the object as unidentified (Class 3).
witness description: The witness observed the object alone and noted its rapid movement and brightness.
